messages.content: **6. Point 2: On New Frontiers**
Voreverl wakes up with Furn carrying her over his shoulder and running.
"Gwehuh...? Oh, are we avoiding payment...? Good, yeah, nice work. Voreverl Leocot is perfectly capable of running on my own, though." Voreverl has no enthusiasm in her voice.

"Yeah, they're a lot smarter than I gave them credit for." Furn ducks into an alleyway to put you down, then keeps running. "We might have lost them by now, but it would probably be the safest option to get out of town."
Voreverl follows Furn "...Yeah, that's fine. This place makes me sick, anyway."

The two of you reach the outskirts of town, at which point Furn again hides in an alleyway to catch his breath which he doesn't have and let you do so.

"We've lost them by now. I assume."
"Great... That, uh, shows them for challenging me..." Voreverl begins idly fiddling with her items "...So, about how long did it take for Bern to come back last time? Are we... getting close?"
Furn makes an exhaust vent noise. "I don't know. I don't even think it was a full day last time."
"Oh, I see... Hey, uh, Furn. You haven't... heard anything about me recently, right?"

"No. I--"

Furn is interrupted as a woman turns the corner into this alleyway. He enters a defensive stance.
"Hello. Sorry to interrupt. Is there a 'Voreverl Leocot' here?"

"I, uh, that's... y-yes, I'm..." Voreverl slaps herself across the face and then points at the woman "Gweheheh! Indeed, you have entered the presence of Voreverl Leocot! Are you a fan, or perhaps, do you wish to challenge the dark overlord of evil to end my reign!? A foolish endeavor for a foolish woman!"
((no way kyrie ushiromiya))
"Hmm. I suppose a fan would be the best answer. I'm Katrielle. I watched the... well, whatever exactly you'd call it. From yesterday."
"We can skip the weird name hang-ups. I don't really give a damn about that. You're Voreverl Leocot to me. That's enough."
Voreverl clenches her fists "...That's... Of course I am... What else would I be!? Are you just here to spout gibberish or do you actually want something!?"
"There's no need to be so uptight. I just thought you'd be more comfortable if I dismissed it from the get-go rather than leaving things unsaid. I want to help you."
"Oh, that's... Gweheheh! Of course you do! Pledging loyalty as a minion of Voreverl Leocot is the only logical choice for any creature with half a brain!"
"I... yeah. Sure."
"..." Voreverl looks around for a moment "So, uh, new minion! What do you think you can provide someone advanced as Voreverl Leocot!?"
"Transport, for one thing. You're not going to get any conquest done on foot."
"That's... true." Voreverl sighs "So, what, you can teleport us or something?"
"Ultimately, yes. With my assistance, you'll be able to be anywhere at your convenience."
"I don't suppose 'anywhere' would include Earth?"
"Not that I'm aware of. I didn't really get that part of the show."
"I didn't want to lead with it while I was still just a suspicious intruder, but it's not really something worth hiding. You know Intuition Overdrive, right? From that whole spectacle?"

Voreverl looks notably annoyed "Ugh, that utter incompetent failure isn't even worth discussing! The fact that I haven't already forgotten about him is my one weakness as an evil ruler! Why are you bringing him up!?"

"Heh. I've never seen anyone get such a thorough and complete read on him in so little time. Well done. I just meant that I can maneuver my way into accessing more or less all of his obscenely versatile connections to organized crime."
"Because he's my son, I mean."
"...Oh." Voreverl turns around and begins to walk away "Furn, we're leaving."
"Okay." Furn follows.
"I see. How unfortunate. How about this, then?"
"Accept my help or I'll get you sent to jail."
"Yeah, sure, whatever. Bern can deal with that when he gets back." Voreverl keeps walking.
"No, he will not." Furn stops.
"I could take or leave the tin man, really. That's not very important. But I guess I should've thought that through. You wouldn't really care about going to jail here, right?"
"You'll be gone from this world later the same way he is now. So I just need to be able to ruin you there too, right?"

Voreverl stops, and after a moment, turns around and begins angrily shouting "Ruin me!? Yeah, good luck making my life any worse than it is now! I just... I just wanted people to know my name, to fear my face, to crumple in panic at the very mention of Voreverl Leocot! And now... It's all ruined! It's all fucking ruined! If I couldn't even be Voreverl Leocot here... A place where my past literally doesn't exist, then I don't have a *chance* on Earth! So yeah, go ahead, do whatever you want! I! Don't! Care!"
"And what the hell makes you think that's impossible here? Are you giving up, pussy?"
"I was excited to find someone both motivated and competent, but I'll be quite disheartened if both are wrong."

"You... You know exactly why it's impossible! Who the fuck fears someone named Jane! Who could ever treat me like a villain when I have such an embarrassing history! I can't *be* Voreverl Leocot anymore! Everyone knows it's... it's not... I'm not..." Voreverl is tearing up now "Just go away! All of you! Stop pretending like you can see me as Voreverl!"
"Aiding you is merely a courtesy. I am obviously not going to leave." Furn.
"Mm. Quite the fix you've found yourself in. I can't afford to quit either, unfortunately. This is my last resort. If I can't succeed now, I'll die as nothing."
"Why did you answer yes when I asked if you knew Intuition Overdrive?"
"Are you an idiot!? You saw me on that farce of a game show! What, do you think I could've lied about that!? 'Oh, no, that was my identical twin Vorgutersloh Aquariuspoly', something like that!?"
“No, that’s not what I was insinuating. Though that would be pretty funny.” https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/963158984913735742/1021151361947160676/unknown.png
“I’m asking why you believe there was anyone of that description with you on that occasion.”
"Wh... Because... There was??? You can't gaslight me! Is this your new strategy to convincing me to join you!? Get me to doubt my sanity!?"

“Groverfield. One of the questions was about a family with that name, and Intuition answered under the premise that it was his family. So ‘Intuition Overdrive’ wouldn’t be the name he was born with, right?”
“I also wouldn’t have personally chose to name a kid Intuition, but that’s neither here nor there.”
((I would name a kid Intuition.))
"...Okay, so what? You're telling me that he's not actually Intuition Overdrive? He's John Groverfield or whatever? Great, real helpful! I'm so happy to know I wasn't the only poser there!"
“No, I don’t give a damn about that. I’m saying you didn’t pick up on it. It’s not quite as bombastic and obnoxiously delivered, but it was still a whole question in the broadcast.”
“And that’s for Intuition Overdrive, who’s kind of notorious. You don’t even have that. Your worries contradict each other.”

“You’re absolutely right. Nobody knows Voreverl Leocot. Nobody fears her or gives a shit about her at this point. I only remembered your name and searched for you for my own potential benefit. So why would they keep track of trivia about this absolute nobody?”

“You don’t have nearly that high staying power. When you’ve just implied you want to do things rather than actually doing anything, I guarantee none of the attention deficit morons that suck up to Neko have any awareness of you.”

"..." Voreverl punches the wall of the alleyway "Gweh... Gwehah... GWEHAHAHAH! You're right! You're absolutely right! If Voreverl Leocot isn't a household name, then neither is... is... that other person! I'm still at square zero! This is my villain origin story! That idiotic buffoon of a woman will regret ever even trying to claim that I would ever not be Voreverl Leocot! First I'll rise to infamy, and then enact my revenge on her! And when the history books tell tales of the bloodshed, it shall be Voreverl Leocot that they say commanded the army of evil!"
https://tenor.com/view/evangelion-clapping-clapping-hands-japan-sea-gif-13300627
"Well said."
"Okay." Furn.

Voreverl raises her fist in the air "Alright! Voreverl Leocot is back on track! No, that's not it, I actually never left! So then, what do you need me for? You've proven yourself incredibly intelligent for managing to reason that out before even I could, so I'll hear out your plans."

"We need to get the hell out of here. For both me and you, doing something attention grabbing in this area would be a bad idea. My son's waste of federal effort is the best option for exiting this corner of Arctica quickly."
"Ugh, relying on that buffoon doesn't sound very glamorous for a villainous plan... But, I suppose it's not *my* plan." Voreverl shrugs "Alright, let's get out of this frigid wasteland."

"I have no desire to defend my son against this sort of slander. ...I care for him, obviously, in my own way, but he really is an idiot. I only want to clarify that the resources he has inherited access to are no joke. This will work."

"Isn't that always how it is... First senile old men like Joe Biden get presidency and laser swords, and now a fool like Intuition gets power in Arctica. Gweheheh, I guess I should be thankful. The underdog villains always come out on top!"
"Shall we be off, then? It's best if we don't linger."
"Of course, a true villain must be omnipresent, I can't afford to lose time being shackled to this primitive town!" Voreverl sets off in a direction without asking what way they're going.
Furn follows silently, having been usurped as the most important NPC in this scene.
"No idea how you knew it was this way, but alright."
They be walking ((end session))
You make it to the "mafia place", a location that Intuition Overdrive has forced to be officially and unshakably recorded as part of the transcript of reality.
"Gweheheh, so, what's the plan here? We break in and steal what we need? Or we swindle it out of them through deceit and betrayal?"
"No, none of that. We just... hmph." She stops short after entering the building.
"Just... what? Listen, I'm all for keeping plans close to your chest, much easier for betrayal, but if you want to be part of my organization, I'm gonna need you to spit it out."
"No, it's... nothing. The woman at the desk just isn't the same one I knew. That shouldn't be a problem." She walks ahead to talk to this mafiosa.
Voreverl follows "Gweheheh! Greetings, fellow villain! I, Voreverl Leocot, have come with my new minion to make use of your services for my evil schemes!"
"Uh, yeah, anyway. There should be teleportation available from here, right?"
The receptionist(?) stares. "Who the hell are you."
"I'm Katrielle Groverfield...? And this is, um... well, you heard her. We're together."
"Never heard of you." The receptionist shoos the two of you away.

Katrielle turns to you.

"You're like... an adult, right? It's hard to tell for sure at my age. Just want to be sure I don't need to pull any punches. You seem pretty gung-ho about all this."
"...Huh, I never really though to ask how old this body is. Whatever, it doesn't matter, I'm an adult back on Earth, so no matter what appearance, I carry the same maturity and wisdom of age!"
"Okay, that's good."
Katrielle stabs the receptionist in the pinky with a pocket knife. She screams.
"Does the name feel familiar enough now? Please, let me talk to your superior so I can stop there."
Voreverl takes a step back "Wh... Whoa... That... Gweheh! Heh! Uh, good work, minion! No one denies Voreverl Leocot access and gets away with it intact!"
The receptionist barely makes out some sentence fragments between screaming. "He... gaagh! Not here... communication with... it's down."
"Really? What an irresponsible man. Whoever he is. Hey, don't just pull that out, dummy, get a compress first."
"So, what, we have to go track down this guy now? Ugh, it's the schemes that are meant to be complicated! Not just getting from one place to another."

The receptionist tends to her wound, but does not budge in refusing you access.

"I don't think this nobody knows a thing about how teleportation works. But really, the boss MIA...? And I couldn't get a hold of Intuition either. Whatever. We can either break through this place by force, or I could try a different, less reliable way of getting where we need to go. It's a matter of priorities. Physical vs. Metaphysical danger."

"Ah... Uh, well..." Voreverl thinks for a moment "As obviously powerful as I am in a fight, as any true villain should be, I'd rather save my debut performance of my skillful battle prowess for a more important, climactic event! What's this other method?"
((wow i am SO good at juggling responsibilities))
"There's a location I should still be capable of bringing us to, a little more out of the way. I'm a little rusty, but it'll be fine. Probably."
"You've proven yourself capable as a minion, I'll place my trust in you. That is, until I find reason for betrayal, of course. Besides, what's a villain origin story without a little risk!"

Katrielle focuses. And a crashing noise is heard. Some kind of teleportation happened, at least.

Voreverl finds herself staring up at an unfamiliar ceiling.
"Gweh? That was quick!" Voreverl shoots up and looks around.
This looks like the room of a young girl.
"...What. Ugh, she must have misunderstood. Children's rooms are *creepy*, not *villainous*. Big difference!" Voreverl tries to leave the room.
The room is not locked. She exits into a hallway full of doors like the one she just exited. This place appears to be in disrepair.

Voreverl groans "How the hell are we supposed to intimidate the heroes if our villainous lair is in such poor condition!? There better be some reason for stopping here, or else I'll need to think of a sufficient punishment for that minion." Voreverl begins looking through the rooms.

Her search is interrupted by Katrielle.

"Sorry about that. Are you alright?"
"Gweheh, of course I'm fine! Voreverl Leocot has survived far more dangerous situations! Anyway, what exactly... *is* this place? Certainly not the most pristine location for evildoing."
"It's a whole thing. Have you heard of Pierce's Academy for Women?"

"Uhhh, no? I've only been in this dimension for like, a couple days. But look, if you're about to go into a big rant about this place, save it. All I need to know is if there's any reason we had to stop at such a dingy place."
"That wasn't my intention, no. It's a dump of a building and it's shut down now. The end. It happens to be a place I could bring us to."

"In that case, let's find my other minion, and get the hell out of here. As they say, time is money, which they also say is the root of all evil, and thus wasting time would be wasting evil!" Voreverl looks around the building for Furn.
"Oh. I almost forgot about him. He should be somewhere around." She also searches.
